->In order to run an angular js project which has AJAX requests (routing, ng-includes, templateUrls, etc.)  we need to create a server.
->one way of creating a server is by using NPM i.e if you are using Node.js
->First Install the server using the command npm install -g http-server
->After installation cd into your project folder and run http-server -o
->-o is to open browser to the page
->now run the index.html page

------------Now your angular js project is ready to run----------------------------------------------------
